    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cajun-style-brown-rice-with-spiced-basa-and-lime-mayo/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice your<strong> brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>black beans</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cajun-style-brown-rice-with-spiced-basa-and-lime-mayo/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> and <strong>chopped pepper</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 8-10 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cajun-style-brown-rice-with-spiced-basa-and-lime-mayo/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>mayo </strong>to a bowl with the juice of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lime[s]</strong>, a small drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and plenty of <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>lime mayo</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lime</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cajun-style-brown-rice-with-spiced-basa-and-lime-mayo/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika</strong> to<strong> </strong>a large bowl with your<strong> ground coriander</strong>,<strong> cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and<strong> dried thyme</strong></p><p>Add a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper </strong>and stir it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>Cajun-style spice mix</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>fish fillet[s]</strong> into bite-sized pieces and pat dry</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cajun-style-brown-rice-with-spiced-basa-and-lime-mayo/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the<strong> </strong>onion<strong> </strong>and<strong> </strong>pepper have softened, add the <strong>drained black beans </strong>to the pan with<strong> half</strong> the <strong>Cajun-style spice mix </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), the<strong> chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong></p><p>Mix it all together and cook for 1 min or until fragrant, then transfer to the pot with the cooked rice</p><p>Give everything a good mix up, then cover and set aside (reserve the pan!) \u2013 this is your <strong>Cajun-style rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cajun-style-brown-rice-with-spiced-basa-and-lime-mayo/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>fish pieces </strong>to the bowl with the <strong>remaining Cajun-style spice mix</strong>,<strong> </strong>1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>flour</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and mix it all together<strong> </strong>\u2013<strong> </strong>these are your <strong>spiced fish pieces</strong></p><p>Return the reserved pan to a high heat with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and<strong> </strong>once hot, add the <strong>spiced</strong> <strong>fish pieces </strong>and cook for 3-4 min each side, or until cooked through (cooking for 3 or more? You may need to do this in batches!)</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cajun-style-brown-rice-with-spiced-basa-and-lime-mayo/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Cajun-style rice</strong> topped with the <strong>spiced fish pieces</strong> and drizzle over the<strong> lime mayo</strong></p><p>Garnish with a <strong>lime wedge</strong> and season with <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
